Canada ‚ÄòSurprised‚Äô By NYC Migrants Bussed To Border

Quebec immigration officials are puzzled after New York City Mayor Eric Adams revealed plans to move on migrants from his city towards the Canadian border.

An existing treaty between Washington and Ottawa requires migrants to register claims in the first country they arrive in before moving to the other, but can only be enforced at official border crossings; NYC officials are reportedly giving free bus tickets to migrants to a famous unofficial border crossing, meaning the burden of processing them can be handed over to Canadian officials. 

Adams claimed in January that there is ‚Äúno more room‚Äù for migrants in New York after visiting Texas border towns that have struggled to cope with record numbers of crossings.
